  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some side dishes for tortellini?",
  "response": "Tortellini can be paired with a variety of side dishes to complement its flavors. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Garlic Bread**: Perfect for mopping up sauce, garlic bread is a classic pairing.\n\n2. **Caprese Salad**: Fresh tomatoes, mozzarella, and basil drizzled with balsamic glaze provide a refreshing contrast.\n\n3. **Roasted Vegetables**: Seasonal vegetables like zucchini, bell peppers, and asparagus roasted with olive oil and herbs can be a healthy and colorful side.\n\n4. **Caesar Salad**: Crisp romaine lettuce, croutons, and Caesar dressing offer a crunchy and creamy side that contrasts nicely with the pasta.\n\n5. **Steamed Broccoli or Green Beans**: Simple yet nutritious, lightly steamed green vegetables provide a nice balance to the dish.\n\n6. **Bruschetta**: Toasted bread topped with a mixture of diced tomatoes, onion, garlic, and basil adds a flavorful accent.\n\n7. **Antipasto Platter**: An assortment of cured meats, olives, cheeses, and marinated vegetables can create a delightful starter or side.\n\n8. **Spinach Salad**: A fresh spinach salad with nuts, dried cranberries, and a light vinaigrette can add a nutritious element.\n\n9. **Minestrone Soup**: A light soup filled with vegetables and beans can be a warming side.\n\n10. **Arugula Salad**: Peppery arugula with lemon dressing and shaved parmesan can add a zesty touch.\n\nThese sides can enhance the tortellini experience while providing a variety of flavors and textures!",
